Package: gplite
Title: Lightweight interface to the most common Gaussian process models
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(person("Juho", "Piironen", role = c("cre", "aut"), email = "juho.t.piironen@gmail.com"))
Description: 
  Implements a lightweight interface to type-II maximum likelihood and Markov chain Monte Carlo 
  inference for Gaussian Process (GP) models using Stan. New observation models and covariance 
  functions are easy to add.
Depends: 
  R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports: 
  methods,
  Rcpp (>= 0.12.0),
  rstan (>= 2.18.1),
  rstantools (>= 2.0.0)
LinkingTo: 
    BH (>= 1.66.0),
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.0),
    RcppEigen (>= 0.3.3.3.0),
    rstan (>= 2.18.1),
    StanHeaders (>= 2.18.0)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: TRUE
Biarch: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
SystemRequirements: GNU make

